# TypeScript React Styling Rules

## Font Family Rules

- Avoid specifying `font-['Inter:Regular',_sans-serif]` as it should be the default
- Only specify font-family when using non-default fonts like `font-['Inter:Medium',_sans-serif]`
- Ensure font-family matches font-weight (Inter:Regular with font-normal, Inter:Medium with font-medium)

## Tailwind Class Preferences

- Use `leading-normal` instead of `leading-[normal]`
- Use standard font size classes instead of arbitrary values:
  - `text-[12px]` → `text-xs`
  - `text-[14px]` → `text-sm`
  - `text-[16px]` → `text-base`
  - `text-[18px]` → `text-lg`
  - `text-[20px]` → `text-xl`
  - `text-[24px]` → `text-2xl`

## Spacing Classes

- Use semantic spacing classes when available:
  - `p-[4px]` → `p-1`
  - `p-[8px]` → `p-2`
  - `m-[4px]` → `m-1`
  - `m-[8px]` → `m-2`

## Example Transformation

❌ Before:

```tsx
<div className="font-['Inter:Regular',_sans-serif] font-normal text-[16px] leading-normal">
  <p className="leading-[normal]">Text</p>
</div>
```

✅ After:

```tsx
<div className="text-base">
  <p className="leading-normal">Text</p>
</div>
```

## Width and Height Measurements

- Convert pixel values to rem using the 16px base:
  - `w-[278px]` → `w-[17.375rem]`
  - `h-[48px]` → `h-[3rem]`
  - `min-w-[120px]` → `min-w-[7.5rem]`
  - `max-w-[400px]` → `max-w-[25rem]`

## Color System Rules

- **NEVER use hardcoded colors** like `text-gray-500`, `bg-gray-100`, `border-gray-200`
- **ALWAYS use design system semantic colors**:
  - `text-foreground` for primary text (instead of `text-gray-950`, `text-black`)
  - `text-muted-foreground` for secondary text (instead of `text-gray-500`, `text-gray-600`)
  - `bg-background` for main backgrounds (instead of `bg-white`)
  - `bg-muted` for subtle backgrounds and hover states (instead of `bg-gray-100`, `bg-gray-50`)
  - `border-border` for borders (instead of `border-gray-200`, `border-gray-300`)
  - `text-muted-foreground` for icons (instead of `text-gray-400`, `text-gray-600`)

## Color Transformation Examples

❌ Before (hardcoded colors):

```tsx
<div className="bg-white border border-gray-200">
  <h1 className="text-gray-950">Title</h1>
  <p className="text-gray-600">Description</p>
  <button className="hover:bg-gray-100 text-gray-500">Action</button>
</div>
```

✅ After (design system colors):

```tsx
<div className="bg-background border border-border">
  <h1 className="text-foreground">Title</h1>
  <p className="text-muted-foreground">Description</p>
  <button className="hover:bg-muted text-muted-foreground">Action</button>
</div>
```

## Table Component Usage

- **ALWAYS use the Table component** instead of custom flex layouts
- Use `Table`, `TableHeader`, `TableBody`, `TableRow`, `TableHead`, `TableCell`
- Apply proper column widths using rem units
- Use semantic colors for all text and backgrounds
